      "options": {
        "code": { "language": "plaintext", "showLineNumbers": false },
        "content": "## Flight Booking System - Monitoring Reference\n\n### Architecture\nFour Python microservices communicate via Apache Kafka:\n`API Gateway` -> `Booking Service` + `Seat Service` -> `Payment Service` -> `Notification Service`\n\n### Key Metrics to Watch\n| Metric | Normal | Warning | Critical |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Booking Success Rate | > 95% | 90-95% | < 90% |\n| DLQ Messages | 0 | 1-5 | > 5 |\n| Payment p95 Latency | < 3s | 3-10s | > 10s |\n| Seat Lock p95 Latency | < 10ms | 10-50ms | > 50ms |\n| Active Seat Locks | < 100 | 100-500 | > 500 |\n| Stripe API Health | 1 (Healthy) | - | 0 (Degraded) |\n\n### Debugging Runbook\n1. **DLQ spike** -> Check Kafka UI at http://localhost:8080 -> Topic `booking.failed.dlq` -> inspect raw messages\n2. **Stripe errors** -> Check `payment_service_stripe_errors_total` by `error_code` - `rate_limit` means back-pressure needed\n3. **Seat conflicts spike** -> Frontend showing stale availability data - check Redis key count at redis-cli DBSIZE\n4. **Service DOWN** -> Check `docker compose ps` and `docker compose logs <service-name>`\n\n### Service URLs\n- **API Docs (Swagger):** http://localhost:8000/docs\n- **Kafka UI:** http://localhost:8080\n- **Prometheus:** http://localhost:9090\n- **Grafana:** http://localhost:3000",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Monitoring Reference & Runbook",
      "type": "text"
